data.description: Nestled within the picturesque confines of Newport Beach, this single-story Bonita plan townhome offers the epitome of coastal living. Boasting three bedrooms and two bathrooms across 1,687 square feet, this home stands centralized at the end of a long, scenic greenbelt.   Through the front gate, you'll be greeted by a tranquil, private front patio, framed with tall greenery. Stepping through the large front door, you'll discover an open-concept floor plan with soaring high ceilings and natural light creating an airy ambiance.  The heart of the home is the well-appointed kitchen, featuring stainless steel appliances. A separate laundry and storage room ensures your home remains organized.  The primary bedroom contains French doors that lead out to the front patio, allowing you to wake up with a cup of coffee and enjoy your private outdoor sitting area. The largely expandable back patio is ready for guest, BBQ’s and entertainment.   With skylights, ample windows, high ceilings, large front and back patios, an open concept design, community pools, private driveway, attached garage and location on a large greenbelt, this home is ready for your final touches.   Located near the Newport Beach Tennis Club, Newport Beach Country Club, and popular beaches, you'll have easy access to top-notch amenities. Indulge in delightful dining experiences at the area's finest restaurants, explore award-winning schools, and take advantage of the proximity to John Wayne airport. For a dose of high-end retail therapy, the renowned Fashion Island and South Coast Plaza are just moments away. Embark on a myriad of outdoor adventures with a range of activities to choose from. Cruise through the harbor, hike along scenic trails, enjoy biking, or indulge in water sports like sailing, fishing, and surfing. Unwind under the sun on pristine beaches or explore the numerous golf courses, spas, and theaters in the area. With a combination of local amenities and coastal charm, this home is truly a haven for those seeking the ideal Southern California coastal lifestyle.
